Man arrested after car chase through Timaru
CHRIS HYDE
Last updated10:06, May 3 2016
MONIQUE FORD/FAIRFAX NZ
Police abandoned the pursuit after the man went through stop signs at intersections on Hassall St at speed.
A Timaru man has been arrested after allegedly acceleratingthrough multiple stop signs on Hassall St in a bid to escape police.Senior SergeantAnthony Callon, of Timaru, said the21-year-old was driving a Toyota Hilux Surf through the suburb ofWest End about 12.10am on Tuesday when police attempted to pull him over.The man accelerated away from them, driving for several kilometres through Timaru's urban area at speed.Police abandoned the pursuit after he went through the stop signsbecause it was too dangerous.Callon said policerang the owner of theSurf who gave them the Timaruaddress of the man who had borrowed his car.The 21-year-oldwas found and arrested a short time after.He was charged with failing to stop and dangerous driving and was to appear in court. The Surf was impounded for 28 days.
